snippet: A surge of violence that left 51 dead and hundreds injured raised new questions about the ability of the interim government to secure the fractured country.
abstract: At least 51 people are killed and hundreds injured as street clashes erupt in several Egyptian cities; surge of violence raises new questions about ability of interim government to secure the fractured country.

byline.original: By MAYY EL SHEIKH and KAREEM FAHIM
byline.contributor: Mayy El Sheikh reported from Cairo, and Kareem Fahim from London.

lead_paragraph: A surge of violence that left 51 dead and hundreds injured raised new questions about the ability of the interim government to secure the fractured country.

headline.main: Dozens Are Killed in Street Violence Across Egypt
